# Implementation Plan: Work Log Visualization Dashboard

The goal is to create a dynamic, visually "premium" dashboard (Kaggle Notebook) that tracks agent activities, tactics, and ML research progress by parsing [WORK_LOG.md](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/new-challenge/WORK_LOG.md), [WORKING_FALL.md](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/new-challenge/WORKING_FALL.md), and research artifacts.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> The dashboard script will use local Kaggle API credentials to push updates. Ensure `KAGGLE_USERNAME` and `KAGGLE_KEY` in [.env](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/new-challenge/.env) are correct.

## Proposed Changes

### [Dashboard Engine]
#### [NEW] [dashboard_generator.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/new-challenge/Usisivac/dashboard_generator.py)
A Python script that:
- Parses [WORK_LOG.md](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/new-challenge/WORK_LOG.md) for daily activity counts and milestones.
- Parses [WORKING_FALL.md](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/new-challenge/WORKING_FALL.md) for task completion percentages (using checkbox states).
- Parses [research_report.md](file:///home/kizabgd/.gemini/antigravity/brain/34bf72c1-fd6d-4cfe-bb89-09758da12e93/research_report.md) for SOTA tactics.
- Generates a Jupyter Notebook `usisivac_dashboard.ipynb` using `nbformat`.
- Injects Plotly-based visualizations (Gantt charts for tasks, pie charts for categories, time-series for activity).

### [Monitoring System]
#### [NEW] [monitor_dashboard.sh](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/new-challenge/monitor_dashboard.sh)
A shell script intended to be run in a Gemini CLI terminal that:
- Watches the log files for changes.
- Automatically triggers `dashboard_generator.py` upon changes.
- Uses `kaggle kernels push` to keep the online notebook updated (if required).

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `python3 Usisivac/dashboard_generator.py` and verify the output `usisivac_dashboard.ipynb` is valid.
- Verify that Markdown parsing correctly identifies `[x]` vs `[ ]` tasks.

### Manual Verification
- Open the generated `.ipynb` file to check visualization aesthetics.
- Verify that terminal output from the monitor script correctly tracks log updates.
